The Secretary to Ogun State Government, Barrister Taiwo Adeoluwa, has been hospitalized after he was involved in a fatal accident on Friday evening. In the tragic incident, one of the prominent aides of Governor Ibikunle Amosun and former Special Adviser on Political Affairs, Prince Adeniyi Adesanya, lost his life. Adesanya, until his death, was popularly called “Friend of the Governor.” Saturday Telegraph gathered that the accident occurred at Siun area, along the Abeokuta-Sagamu Expressway, while the duo were returning from Lagos. Eyewitnesses account said an unidentified vehicle rammed into Adeoluwa’s vehicle, forcing it to lose control on top speed. The victims were said to have been rushed to the Federal Medical Centre (FMC), Idi-Aba, Abeokuta. A highly placed source at the hospital confirmed to our correspondent that the SSG had been transferred to the Intensive Care Unit. “News of the accident is true. We lost Friend of the Governor (Adesanya); it’s so sad. The SSG was injured but we thank God he is alive,” an official of the state government told our correspondent last night. The official, who craved anonymity, disclosed that the SSG and the late aide were returning from Lagos after carrying out an assignment of the governor.